title: Sidewall, 1835–45
provenance: Found in north stair hall, 2nd floor on east wall of Rose Hill, built 1839,Geneva, New York.
creditline: Gift of Geneva Historical Society, Geneva, NY
description: Brown, rust and white on tan grounded paper. Large brick-like rectangles in all-over arrangement like diagonal or plumb bonded bricks. Each rectangle formed of lines arranged to give effect of shading imitating a raised stone or wooden panel. Space between rectangles filled with solid, darker brown.

tombstone.epitaph:
Sidewall, 1835–45.
1835–45. Machine-printed (?). Gift of Geneva Historical Society, Geneva, NY. 1968-65-1-a,b.
